y. worked fine on .NET 10. The jump to v3 in .NET 11 would break it. Let me verify what Sandy Bridge actually supports—it has all the v2 requirements like SSE4.2 and POPCNT, but it's missing AVX2, BMI1, BMI2, and FMA, so it definitely doesn't meet the v3 baseline.\n\nThis explains the situation perfectly: 2012-era hardware like Sandy and Ivy Bridge can run v2 but not v3, which is why the upgrade breaks compatibility on that generation.","outputTokens":2610,"requestId":"400B:1EC1:11351D4:13B32A1:69F94A6E"},"id":"e93b5364-5117-4464-8d3f-1ec1f802f1a6","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:40:47.791Z","parentId":"f0c52889-3508-462b-a366-a5ab724ca9b8"}
